About Me

Passionate.

Hi, I'm Anne Mwachaka — a passionate and detail-oriented software developer with a strong interest in building impactful, user-centered web systems.

I enjoy transforming ideas into functional, responsive, and scalable applications that solve real-world problems. My focus is on clean code, structured system design, and creating seamless user experiences from front-end to back-end.

I am continuously learning and improving my technical and problem-solving skills, with a goal of building innovative digital solutions that make a difference.

Featured Work

Project Showcase

Completed & Live

Viazibora

"Bridging agriculture and technology to create smarter marketplaces."

Viazibora is a full-stack web application designed to facilitate the online sale and distribution of potatoes. The system implements user authentication, product management, order processing, and structured database storage to support secure and efficient transactions.

The system demonstrates practical implementation of software development principles — from requirements analysis and system design through database modeling and seamless front-to-back integration.
